					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wouldn't it make more sense to keep the stack pointer in x at all times? Then code could access stack variables via $500-i,x, where i is the index of the local. For example, if it has three locals, it accesses them as $500,x  $4FF,x and $4FE,x. That makes them much more convenient and efficient to use.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

